				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Voice of the Vampire (70) question<a name="71783"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 3 05 3:20 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The level 70 Charm.
<br />

<br />
Every charm that I've used up through the level 64 charm looks like this charm. Every charm that I've used so far hasn't needed any sort of flute...at all. The only song that requires a flute is the invisibility song, which you'll want for swarming until you can get your hands on some Mosquito Boots, and the only song that uses flute mod is the Song of Dawn, which reduces a mob's hate toward you. I'm sure there are others, so reply to this to increase the collective knowledge about the general weirdness of flouting.
<br />

<br />
Anyway, if you look at the raw data on lucy.allakhazam.com you'll see that all of the charms look similar.
<br />

<br />
The only differences are mana cost *AND* the big back-breaker, the range of 30 of the level 70 charm. This means that you'll die too often while swarming because 30 feet away from 15 mobs in a Tier 4 plane means a 95% chance of sudden death, with a few rain showers. You'd have to be friggin' good to use this as a tool for quick xp swarming. I had a lot of trouble landing the level 2 Lute song while circling cougars, which has a range of 25, but found it much easier with the level 18 brass song, which has a range of 35. The big difference is that those level 30'ish mobs have a small range of attack and you could actually auto-circle them if you had a good computer and Internet connection. Level 60'ish mobs are much bigger and have a larger melee range. You'd also have to time exactly when you're going to get close enough to the mobs with the casting time.
<br />

<br />
Mostly I see the 70 charm as a 60-second mez that can triple our DPS. Otherwise, we have to spend a twist with our bard-mez, which only lasts 18 seconds.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">Tuskin of Saryrn</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
